snippet.textDisplay:
The whole point; stream like a human ;)
1. Video quality 480p or over
2. DO NOT mute the video
3. Be logged into your YouTube account while viewing
4. DO NOT rewind the video
5. Don’t speed OR skip through the video
6. If there’s an ad watch until the end
7. DO NOT press the replay button. Watch a different video, leave YouTube, and research the desired video in the search bar. REPEAT
8. If you have multiple accounts, switch between them
9. DO NOT use playlists
10. DO NOT delete your history for that video, all of your views WILL be deleted!
11. ENJOY THE MUSIC!!! They’ve worked really hard on this and they want you to ENJOY. Have fun, dance around a bit ;)

MYTHS:
“Using words like stream, view, or emoji in he comment section freezes the video” It does absolutely NOTHING. YouTube freezes views to check if the views are real. If there are a lot of views it takes time. So when views freeze, it’s a good sign—it means many ARMYs are watching the video :)

Notes:
You can only watch it 50x per day per IP address (you can watch it on multiple accounts though)

I read this on the web;

Experts believe that after 4 or 5 views in one day, YouTube stops adding new views to a video’s view count number. If there’s anything wrong with what I wrote, please correct me in the comments :) I PURPLE YOUUUUUUU💜
